Promotional material for acrobatic show Clothing of Birds Photo: Courtesy of the Ministry of Culture and TourismNanning in South China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region will host China's 10th Acrobatic Performance Season from July 17 to 28, China's Ministry of Culture and Tourism announced on Wednesday.  A total of 40 acrobatic programs and acrobatic dramas will be staged at theaters across the city. According to ministry representative Ming Wenjun, this is the first time acrobatic dramas will be part of the season. The programs will cover red themes and China's traditional culture.  To allow more people to attend performances, the season will continue its policy of providing affordable tickets for 50 ($7.25) or 80 yuan.  
